lle AH1]]<br />[[AgustaWestland AW159 Wildcat|Wildcat AH1]]\n| aircraft_trainer = \n| aircraft_transport = \n}}\n\nThe '''1st Aviation Brigade''' is an aviation [[brigade]] of the [[British Army]].<ref name=\"ArmyMay\">{{cite press release |title=Army establishes its 1st Aviation Brigade |url=https://www.army.mod.uk/news-and-events/news/2020/05/army-aviation-brigade/ |website=British Army |accessdate=6 May 2020 |date=5 May 2020}}</ref> Most of its units are from the [[Army Air Corps (United Kingdom)|Army Air Corps]] (AAC). It was stood up on 1 April 2020 by combining the Wattisham Flying Station Headquarters (WFS HQ), formerly the Attack Helicopter Force (AHF) at [[Wattisham Airfield|Wattisham]] and the Aviation Reconnaissance Force at the [[RNAS Yeovilton (HMS Heron)|Royal Naval Air Station Yeovilton]].<ref name=\"ArmyMay\"/><ref>{{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=The Eagle Spring 2020 edition |url=http://www.theeagleonline.co.uk/wp-content/uploads/2020/04/WattishamEagleSpring2020web.pdf |work=The Eagle |location=Wattisham |date=1 April 2020 |access-date=7 May 2020 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Ripley |first=Tim |date=6 April 2020 |title=UK forms aviation brigade |url=https://www.janes.com/article/95356/uk-forms-aviation-brigade |work=IHS Janes |location= |access-date=7 May 2020 }}</ref>\n\n==Structure==\nThe brigade consists of:<ref name=\"ArmyMay\"/>\n\n* 1 Regiment Army AAC\n* 3 Regiment AAC\n* 4 Regiment AAC\n* 5 Regiment AAC - only Gazelle helicopters\n* 6 Regiment AAC\n* 7th Battalion Royal Electrical and Mechanical Engineers\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Army Air Corps}}\n\n[[Category:Brigades of the British Army]]\n[[Category:Aviation units and formations of the British Army]]\n[[Category:Military units and formations established in 2020]]\n[[Category:2020 establishments in the United Kingdom]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2020}}\n{{Use British English|date=May 2020}}\n{{Infobox military unit\n| unit_name = 1s